    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7, then take your<strong> chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Cut your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into chips</p><p>Add the <strong>chips</strong> to a baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for an initial 20-25 min or until golden and starting to crisp</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bbq-double-chicken-breast-loaded-cheesy-fries/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely slice most of your <strong>red onion[s]</strong></p><p>Dice the <strong>remaining red onion[s]</strong> finely</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bbq-double-chicken-breast-loaded-cheesy-fries/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your<strong> chicken </strong>with the <strong>sliced onion </strong>(you'll use the remaining chopped onion later!),<strong> half </strong>your <strong>ground smoked paprika </strong>(save the rest for later!) and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Cook for 5-6 min on each side until the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!) and the onion has softened</p><p>(Doubled your protein? Use 2 pans!)</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bbq-double-chicken-breast-loaded-cheesy-fries/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Whilst the chicken is cooking, finely grate your <strong>lighter cheese</strong></p><p>Wash your <strong>lettuce</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper and roughly shred</p><p>Chop your <strong>tomato[es]</strong> finely</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bbq-double-chicken-breast-loaded-cheesy-fries/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>chopped tomato</strong> to a large bowl with the <strong>shredded lettuce</strong> and <strong>remaining chopped onion</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>cider vinegar </strong>and a little drizzle of<strong> olive oil </strong>and toss together \u2013 this is your<strong> salad</strong></p><p>In a separate bowl, combine your<strong> natural</strong> <strong>yoghurt </strong>with the <strong>remaining ground smoked paprika</strong>, your <strong>roasted garlic paste </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>smoky yoghurt</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bbq-double-chicken-breast-loaded-cheesy-fries/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once done, transfer the chicken to a clean board and shred it apart, using two forks \u2013 this technique is known as 'pulling'</p><p>Return the <strong>pulled chicken </strong>to the pan with your<strong> BBQ sauce </strong>and give everything a good mix up \u2013this is your <strong>BBQ pulled chicken</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bbq-double-chicken-breast-loaded-cheesy-fries/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the chips are golden and starting to crisp, push the <strong>chips</strong> into 1 pile per person and top with the <strong>grated lighter cheese</strong></p><p>Return the tray[s] to the oven for a final 4-5 min or until the cheese has melted \u2013 these are your <strong>cheesy fries</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bbq-double-chicken-breast-loaded-cheesy-fries/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> cheesy fries</strong> topped with the <strong>BBQ pulled chicken</strong> with the <strong>salad</strong> to the side</p><p>Drizzle the <strong>smoky yoghurt </strong>over the top</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
